The paper deals with quantum finite automata (QFA), which are a topic in computational complexity theory and quantum computing. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also discusses the language recognition power and succinctness of QFA, which are related to the topics of quantum algorithms and quantum information theory. Hence, cs.QL (Quantum Physics) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also likely categories. The paper also mentions closure properties of related classes, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) possible categories as well.
